  11 class ResourceTests:
  12     # Subclasses are expected to set the `data` attribute.
  13 
  14     def test_is_resource_good_path(self):
  15         self.assertTrue(resources.is_resource(self.data, 'binary.file'))
  16 
  17     def test_is_resource_missing(self):
  18         self.assertFalse(resources.is_resource(self.data, 'not-a-file'))
  19 
  20     def test_is_resource_subresource_directory(self):
  21         # Directories are not resources.
  22         self.assertFalse(resources.is_resource(self.data, 'subdirectory'))
  23 
  24     def test_contents(self):
  25         contents = set(resources.contents(self.data))
  26         # There may be cruft in the directory listing of the data directory.
  27         # Under Python 3 we could have a __pycache__ directory, and under
  28         # Python 2 we could have .pyc files.  These are both artifacts of the
  29         # test suite importing these modules and writing these caches.  They
  30         # aren't germane to this test, so just filter them out.
  31         contents.discard('__pycache__')
  32         contents.discard('__init__.pyc')
  33         contents.discard('__init__.pyo')
  34         self.assertEqual(contents, {
  35             '__init__.py',
  36             'subdirectory',
  37             'utf-8.file',
  38             'binary.file',
  39             'utf-16.file',
  40             })

  52 @unittest.skipIf(sys.version_info < (3,), 'No ResourceReader in Python 2')
  53 class ResourceLoaderTests(unittest.TestCase):
  54     def test_resource_contents(self):
  55         package = util.create_package(
  56             file=data01, path=data01.__file__, contents=['A', 'B', 'C'])
  57         self.assertEqual(
  58             set(resources.contents(package)),
  59             {'A', 'B', 'C'})
  60 
  61     def test_resource_is_resource(self):
  62         package = util.create_package(
  63             file=data01, path=data01.__file__,
  64             contents=['A', 'B', 'C', 'D/E', 'D/F'])
  65         self.assertTrue(resources.is_resource(package, 'B'))
  66 
  67     def test_resource_directory_is_not_resource(self):
  68         package = util.create_package(
  69             file=data01, path=data01.__file__,
  70             contents=['A', 'B', 'C', 'D/E', 'D/F'])
  71         self.assertFalse(resources.is_resource(package, 'D'))
  72 
  73     def test_resource_missing_is_not_resource(self):
  74         package = util.create_package(
  75             file=data01, path=data01.__file__,
  76             contents=['A', 'B', 'C', 'D/E', 'D/F'])
  77         self.assertFalse(resources.is_resource(package, 'Z'))
  78

  80 class ResourceCornerCaseTests(unittest.TestCase):
  81     def test_package_has_no_reader_fallback(self):
  82         # Test odd ball packages which:
  83         # 1. Do not have a ResourceReader as a loader
  84         # 2. Are not on the file system
  85         # 3. Are not in a zip file
  86         module = util.create_package(
  87             file=data01, path=data01.__file__, contents=['A', 'B', 'C'])
  88         # Give the module a dummy loader.
  89         module.__loader__ = object()
  90         # Give the module a dummy origin.
  91         module.__file__ = '/path/which/shall/not/be/named'
  92         if sys.version_info >= (3,):
  93             module.__spec__.loader = module.__loader__
  94             module.__spec__.origin = module.__file__
  95         self.assertFalse(resources.is_resource(module, 'A'))

  98 class ResourceFromZipsTest01(util.ZipSetupBase, unittest.TestCase):
  99     ZIP_MODULE = zipdata01                          # type: ignore
 100 
 101     def test_is_submodule_resource(self):
 102         submodule = import_module('ziptestdata.subdirectory')
 103         self.assertTrue(
 104             resources.is_resource(submodule, 'binary.file'))
 105 
 106     def test_read_submodule_resource_by_name(self):
 107         self.assertTrue(
 108             resources.is_resource('ziptestdata.subdirectory', 'binary.file'))
 109 
 110     def test_submodule_contents(self):
 111         submodule = import_module('ziptestdata.subdirectory')
 112         self.assertEqual(
 113             set(resources.contents(submodule)),
 114             {'__init__.py', 'binary.file'})
 115 
 116     def test_submodule_contents_by_name(self):
 117         self.assertEqual(
 118             set(resources.contents('ziptestdata.subdirectory')),
 119             {'__init__.py', 'binary.file'})

 122 class ResourceFromZipsTest02(util.ZipSetupBase, unittest.TestCase):
 123     ZIP_MODULE = zipdata02                          # type: ignore
 124 
 125     def test_unrelated_contents(self):
 126         # https://gitlab.com/python-devs/importlib_resources/issues/44
 127         #
 128         # Here we have a zip file with two unrelated subpackages.  The bug
 129         # reports that getting the contents of a resource returns unrelated
 130         # files.
 131         self.assertEqual(
 132             set(resources.contents('ziptestdata.one')),
 133             {'__init__.py', 'resource1.txt'})
 134         self.assertEqual(
 135             set(resources.contents('ziptestdata.two')),
 136             {'__init__.py', 'resource2.txt'})

 139 @unittest.skipIf(sys.version_info < (3,), 'No namespace packages in Python 2')
 140 class NamespaceTest(unittest.TestCase):
 141     def test_namespaces_cannot_have_resources(self):
 142         contents = resources.contents(
 143             'importlib_resources.tests.data03.namespace')
 144         self.assertFalse(list(contents))
 145         # Even though there is a file in the namespace directory, it is not
 146         # considered a resource, since namespace packages can't have them.
 147         self.assertFalse(resources.is_resource(
 148             'importlib_resources.tests.data03.namespace',
 149             'resource1.txt'))
 150         # We should get an exception if we try to read it or open it.
 151         self.assertRaises(
 152             FileNotFoundError,
 153             resources.open_text,
 154             'importlib_resources.tests.data03.namespace', 'resource1.txt')
 155         self.assertRaises(
 156             FileNotFoundError,
 157             resources.open_binary,
 158             'importlib_resources.tests.data03.namespace', 'resource1.txt')
 159         self.assertRaises(
 160             FileNotFoundError,
 161             resources.read_text,
 162             'importlib_resources.tests.data03.namespace', 'resource1.txt')
 163         self.assertRaises(
 164             FileNotFoundError,
 165             resources.read_binary,
 166             'importlib_resources.tests.data03.namespace', 'resource1.txt')
